=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains the filter to apply when retrieving metrics with the
GetMetricDataV2
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/connect/latest/APIReference/API_GetMetricDataV2.html)
API.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 FilterKey => Str

The key to use for filtering data. For example, C<QUEUE>,
C<ROUTING_PROFILE, AGENT>, C<CHANNEL>, C<AGENT_HIERARCHY_LEVEL_ONE>,
C<AGENT_HIERARCHY_LEVEL_TWO>, C<AGENT_HIERARCHY_LEVEL_THREE>,
C<AGENT_HIERARCHY_LEVEL_FOUR>, C<AGENT_HIERARCHY_LEVEL_FIVE>. There
must be at least 1 key and a maximum 5 keys.


=head2 FilterValues => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The identifiers to use for filtering data. For example, if you have a
filter key of C<QUEUE>, you would add queue IDs or ARNs in
C<FilterValues>.



